    <span class="section-label">Statement of Faith</span>
    <h2>Rooted in Scripture, United in Belief</h2>
    <p>Miracle Temple is part of the Church of God in Christ (COGIC), and we hold to the following core beliefs as the foundation of our faith and practice.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="belief-list">
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">01</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe the Bible to be the inspired and only infallible written Word of God.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">02</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe that there is only One God, eternally existent in three persons: God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">03</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe in the blessed Hope, which is the rapture of the Church of God, which is in Christ, at His return.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">04</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe that the only means of being cleansed from sin is through repentance and faith in the precious Blood of Jesus Christ.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">05</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe that regeneration by the Holy Ghost is absolutely essential for personal salvation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">06</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe that the redemptive work of Christ on the Cross provides healing for the human body in answer to believing prayer.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">07</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe that the Baptism of the Holy Spirit, according to Acts 2:4, is given to believers who ask for it.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="belief-item">
      <div class="belief-number">08</div>
      <div class="belief-text">We believe in the sanctifying power of the Holy Spirit, by whose indwelling the Christian is enabled to live a holy and separated life in the present world.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="beliefs-source">Statement of Faith of the Church of God in Christ (COGIC)</p>
</section>

